<def f='exim/src/lookups/lf_quote.c' l='30' ll='62' type='gstring * lf_quote(uschar * name, uschar * value, int vlength, gstring * result)'/>
<doc f='exim/src/lookups/lf_quote.c' l='17'>/* This function is called by some lookups that create name=value result
strings, to handle the quoting of the data. It adds &quot;name=&quot; to the result,
followed by appropriately quoted data, followed by a single space.

Arguments:
  name           the field name
  value          the data value
  vlength        the data length
  result         the result expanding-string

Returns:         the result pointer (possibly updated)
*/</doc>
